<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-759-482  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 759 482.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computerworld  Oct 16 1989 v23 n42 p21(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Don't underestimate the importance of Ada. (Ada programminglanguage) (column)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Barnes, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Ada programming language is widely perceived as havingdisappeared from the software scene, but its importance is likelyto increase in the future.andP;  Common misconceptions about Adainclude the belief that its success is entirely dependent on theDepartment of Defense; that Ada applications will remain fewbecause there are few programmers trained in the language; andthat the world needs better design rather than a better language.andO;Hundreds of thousands of programmers with Ada experience will soonemerge from the military, bringing Ada skills to the civilianlabor pool.andP;  The language also facilitates improved design becauseit simplifies the expression of basic design ideas that are clumsyin other languages.andP;  Programming in Ada is excellent training indesign fundamentals.andP;  Ada is also uniquely suited to self-definingcode generation and advanced mathematical applications on embeddedsystems.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     ADAProgramming LanguagesProgram Development TechniquesSoftware Quality.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>